<subSubSection id="C0CC37BBCFA1DF59F21F213F6818B54E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="F86CAD211AA3812DDD32C2CCE4F1CCBA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AAED1F94C408564BFC786BA546140E45" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Australia, Queensland, Beaudesert, from leaf spot on 
<taxonomicName id="6603E7FA5AC5784E2930A4D90C04A4D9" class="Aves" family="Fringillidae" genus="Chloris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chloris gayana" order="Passeriformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gayana">Chloris gayana</taxonomicName>
, 9 Jan. 1974, J.L. Alcorn (holotype BRIP 10972, includes ex-type culture).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D4725401CCA9487DAA352AC07BA744B0" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="122D8D81064B33D41AEA99C1B34872C0" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="934B38E6C886548A3F161C1C66D14980" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="4D42F31E75B1513B6C743054E4327F54" genus="Colonies" lsidName="Colonies" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="genus">Colonies</taxonomicName>
on PDA approx. 4 cm diam. after 7 d at 25 °C, surface funiculose, margin fimbriate, olivaceous black. 
<taxonomicName id="A8441856B373D8BA9FD449FCE1E0EF98" genus="Hyphae" lsidName="Hyphae" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="genus">Hyphae</taxonomicName>
subhyaline, smooth to branched, septate, up to 3 
<normalizedToken id="B247A7D8F4286E8FF849FBC46F6F41D5" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
in width. 
<taxonomicName id="65C56AE7DB9B3BAAFA8C36692D52B6CA" genus="Conidiophores" lsidName="Conidiophores" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="genus">Conidiophores</taxonomicName>
branched, erect, straight to flexuous, geniculate towards apex, brown, paler towards apex, smooth, septate, up to 110 
<normalizedToken id="72606FD17B7E4A77D76C44B41F525E83" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long, 4 
<normalizedToken id="4BBF856A365485683CB880CFD72458F7" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
wide; basal cell swollen and darker than the other cells, up to 6 
<normalizedToken id="AA21AD921C70DCAC216B3E7E740D3E5C" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
diam. 
<taxonomicName id="B4353EE223C6AFF4868BA3DD6237F4C6" genus="Conidiogenous" lsidName="Conidiogenous cells" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="cells">Conidiogenous cells</taxonomicName>
integrated, terminal or intercalary, sympodial, pale brown, smooth, with darkened scars. 
<taxonomicName id="068AF178F5B142FFB210F58EB4BAD67E" authority="" authorityName="" class="Arthoniomycetes" family="Arthoniaceae" genus="Conidia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Conidia" order="Arthoniales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Conidia</taxonomicName>
fusiform, straight to slightly curved, rounded at the apex, (14-) 26-29 (-34) 
<normalizedToken id="0710C0EFFAAF9CC6F4821303E9DEEEB6" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(5-) 6.5-7.5 (-9) 
<normalizedToken id="9EB29D34EFF4D5536C04D0A8322D806B" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, brown to dark brown, 3-7 (mostly 5)-distoseptate; hila conspicuous, slightly protuberant, thickened and darkened, 1−1.5 
<normalizedToken id="5C0065884A61EF760BCB4D04564E11BC" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
wide.
</paragraph>
<caption id="9BF0BA3036E4234D3CAB3E7850A22344" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<paragraph id="12CF6FFBEA11B5860285C262C7B35969" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Figure 2. 
<taxonomicName id="080BB46546A4A41D443A13EC96621683" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Pleosporaceae" genus="Curvularia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Curvularia beasleyi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="beasleyi">Curvularia beasleyi</taxonomicName>
(BRIP 10972): A colony on 
<normalizedToken id="154C7AB59ED5786FD94804B0DE965E64" originalValue="PDAB–C">PDAB-C</normalizedToken>
conidiophores and conidia D conidia. 
<taxonomicName id="F0293A39BD37E80D10B6782C5D771DAD" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Pleosporaceae" genus="Curvularia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Curvularia beerburrumensis" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="beerburrumensis">Curvularia beerburrumensis</taxonomicName>
(BRIP 12942) E colony on PDAF chlamydospores G conidiophore 
<normalizedToken id="848C93CB63A486979A00912B1CC0713C" originalValue="H–I">H-I</normalizedToken>
conidia. 
<taxonomicName id="9F178611B21A1F0084E4DA0FA69B8072" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Pleosporaceae" genus="Curvularia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Curvularia boeremae" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="boeremae">Curvularia boeremae</taxonomicName>
(IMI 164633) J colony on PDAK conidiophores L conidia. 
<taxonomicName id="D309F13FDC1A9A9621BC4AE66BE67F8E" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Pleosporaceae" genus="Curvularia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Curvularia coatesiae" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="coatesiae">Curvularia coatesiae</taxonomicName>
(BRIP 24261) M colony on PDAN conidiophores O conidia. Scale bars: 1 cm (A, E, J, M); all others - 10 
<normalizedToken id="B623F98C205FEE5376C80E81B1098275" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D7256727BB416DF274555F14282B4C43" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="80AB7CD99F7B76A4C24143FA4B30619E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BA41EFFEBC009109656289F8FF5F17F1" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">In recognition of Dr Dean R. Beasley, an Australian plant pathologist, for his dedication and numerous innovative contributions to the curation and promotion of the Queensland Plant Pathology Herbarium (BRIP).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0A7672EDE9214C7091B4037CD37BA530" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="D189BD7EEE59164B3830B08F95616BA9" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Additional material examined.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B571EB80A120F2C018B22A05DC7613B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Australia, Queensland, Atherton, from leaf spot on 
<taxonomicName id="CB3315044DA34A7DBB5BB35B50A5F5D7" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Leersia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Leersia hexandra" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hexandra">Leersia hexandra</taxonomicName>
, 1 May 1987, J.L. Alcorn, BRIP 15854 (includes culture).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="513363A3735AB39C17A3717FE6C38BBF" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="8B1901900C15791642BD3E05B20012E9" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CB8B382DF12F12D57CDFC50F551AAD48" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="42B9391A765B6884A8D327E6A1C9B43D" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Pleosporaceae" genus="Curvularia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Curvularia beasleyi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="beasleyi">Curvularia beasleyi</taxonomicName>
is placed in the same clade as 
<taxonomicName id="0E7B731248977864EE0150BFB512D5E2" genus="C." lsidName="C. dactyloctenii" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="dactyloctenii">C. dactyloctenii</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="55EC85A646BDE857D8B20BCE3AF5D889" genus="C." lsidName="C. hawaiiensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="hawaiiensis">C. hawaiiensis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F2CE656F5897DBE90240033AEC646F0E" genus="C." lsidName="C. nodosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="nodosa">C. nodosa</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 1). 
<taxonomicName id="63060B6517F991CF4C07C2B8AB8215A5" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Pleosporaceae" genus="Curvularia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Curvularia dactyloctenii" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="dactyloctenii">Curvularia dactyloctenii</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="A5B215ADB928E7BC5550641AFC4AD7DA" genus="C." lsidName="C. hawaiiensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="hawaiiensis">C. hawaiiensis</taxonomicName>
have been recorded in Australia (
<bibRefCitation id="D488484AAFC7585C7205B44CC62F312D" author="Sivanesan, A" journalOrPublisher="Mycological Papers" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 261" title="Graminicolous species of Bipolaris, Curvularia, Drechslera, Exserohilum and their teleomorphs." volume="158" year="1987">Sivanesan 1987</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="3338F04178C7538CD9DB74330220DE78" author="Tan, YP" journalOrPublisher="Australasian Plant Pathology" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="589 - 603" title="Johnalcornia gen. et. comb. nov., and nine new combinations in Curvularia based on molecular phylogenetic analysis." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s13313-014-0315-6" volume="43" year="2014">Tan et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
), but the recently described 
<taxonomicName id="BF660F1372EB102660C0452DBC8F9D84" genus="C." lsidName="C. nodosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="nodosa">C. nodosa</taxonomicName>
has only been reported from Thailand (
<bibRefCitation id="5B13EAE73BDE56ADAF615E9EF06CDB5C" author="Marin-Felix, J" journalOrPublisher="Mycosphere" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1556 - 1574" title="New species and records of Bipolaris and Curvularia from Thailand." url="https://doi.org/10.5943/mycosphere/8/9/11" volume="8" year="2017 b">Marin-Felix et al. 2017b</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="38866F36C606A820A20794ACF5869D41" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Pleosporaceae" genus="Curvularia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Curvularia beasleyi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="beasleyi">Curvularia beasleyi</taxonomicName>
is distinguished in two loci from the ex-type cultures of 
<taxonomicName id="7203697F8173E542B7469C35C44C6D71" genus="C." lsidName="C. dactyloctenii" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="dactyloctenii">C. dactyloctenii</taxonomicName>
(99% in gapdh and 99% in tef1α), 
<taxonomicName id="28E968AB6B66FC04869785E991407B5C" genus="C." lsidName="C. hawaiiensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="hawaiiensis">C. hawaiiensis</taxonomicName>
(98% in gapdh and 99% in tef1α) and 
<taxonomicName id="B795E684C678FE8C3C42502FEB767228" genus="C." lsidName="C. nodosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="nodosa">C. nodosa</taxonomicName>
(99% in gapdh and 99% in tef1α). The conidia of 
<taxonomicName id="84B50C84D10F3CCEF9729278B4AF882B" genus="C." lsidName="C. beasleyi" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="beasleyi">C. beasleyi</taxonomicName>
are longer than those of 
<taxonomicName id="F688A7BC05ED2D7F0443C0F6D61B2E05" genus="C." lsidName="C. nodosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="nodosa">C. nodosa</taxonomicName>
(12-25 
<normalizedToken id="93CF81732D34352D4B38F7E704F15E06" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="7A5114ABF1416935D09100AB161F7062" author="Marin-Felix, J" journalOrPublisher="Mycosphere" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1556 - 1574" title="New species and records of Bipolaris and Curvularia from Thailand." url="https://doi.org/10.5943/mycosphere/8/9/11" volume="8" year="2017 b">Marin-Felix et al. 2017b</bibRefCitation>
) and shorter than those of 
<taxonomicName id="DEA40B5EF8D99632E581500B7740047F" genus="C." lsidName="C. dactyloctenii" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="dactyloctenii">C. dactyloctenii</taxonomicName>
(32-55 
<normalizedToken id="1DFBA93577100BA483B847F14EFC48F7" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="C92FD4CB5A98949405F249E0A41914D4" author="Sivanesan, A" journalOrPublisher="Mycological Papers" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 261" title="Graminicolous species of Bipolaris, Curvularia, Drechslera, Exserohilum and their teleomorphs." volume="158" year="1987">Sivanesan 1987</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="2EC451E94B6ABCE804B8666EE492F04D" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Pleosporaceae" genus="Curvularia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Curvularia beasleyi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="beasleyi">Curvularia beasleyi</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="6662B39A3C4323582C54A9B309309F70" genus="C." lsidName="C. hawaiiensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="hawaiiensis">C. hawaiiensis</taxonomicName>
, however the later species has never been recorded on 
<taxonomicName id="91274E71698C7D78B13138DE13AD12DC" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Leersia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Leersia" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Leersia</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8182A6BF51C9EADD8FDAAB1FD8B350FD" author="Farr, DF" journalOrPublisher="Mycoscience" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" url="https://nt.ars-grin.gov/fungaldatabases/" year="2018">Farr and Rossman 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="948BBE7EA05A041A866BD27CA54FD6A7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="B45AE27527978F03D4EF5D3A1773B40D" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Pleosporaceae" genus="Curvularia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Curvularia beasleyi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="beasleyi">Curvularia beasleyi</taxonomicName>
is only known from Queensland on two unrelated grasses, the introduced host 
<taxonomicName id="207E2DDBB1F0765A00216ABDA9AD8E7B" class="Aves" family="Fringillidae" genus="Chloris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chloris gayana" order="Passeriformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gayana">Chloris gayana</taxonomicName>
and the native 
<taxonomicName id="CEF0253166D6596D68D516C76CEFD730" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Leersia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Leersia hexandra" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hexandra">Leersia hexandra</taxonomicName>
. There are many 
